## Common Mistakes

| Mistake | Fix |
|---|---|
| Using href="/path" for SPA navigation | Use data-route + pushState |
| No popstate listener | Add it — breaks browser back/forward button |
| API route registered after SPA wildcard | Always register API routes before * fallback |
| Static files caught by fallback | Register express.static / try_files before SPA fallback |
| Sections visible by default | Add hidden to all sections in HTML; let JS reveal the active one |
| Hardcoded links in HTML (not using router) | All internal navigation must go through navigate() |
| Forgetting to call resolve() on initial load | Call it in DOMContentLoaded |

---

## Checklist

- [ ] Server serves the HTML shell for all non-asset, non-API paths
- [ ] API routes are registered before the SPA fallback
- [ ] pushState used for all internal navigation (no href on SPA links)
- [ ] popstate listener handles browser back/forward
- [ ] resolve() called on DOMContentLoaded for direct URL loads
- [ ] All page sections start as hidden; router reveals the active one
- [ ] Active nav link state updates on every route change
- [ ] A 404 / fallback route is defined for unmatched paths
